# Never Show DB Variables in Public UI

Raw database column values (e.g. `pending_approval`, `in_progress`, `en_route_to_pickup`) must **never** be displayed directly to end users in any client-facing page or component.

## Rule

Always map DB enum/status values to human-readable labels before rendering.

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — exposes raw DB value
<span>{delivery.status}</span>
<option value="pending_approval">pending_approval</option>
<option value="in_progress">in_progress</option>

// ✅ GOOD — use a label map
const STATUS_LABELS: Record<string, string> = {
  pending_approval: "Pending Acceptance",
  in_progress: "In Progress",
  en_route_to_pickup: "En Route to Pickup",
  completed: "Completed",
};
<span>{STATUS_LABELS[delivery.status] ?? delivery.status}</span>
<option value="pending_approval">Pending Acceptance</option>
```

## Applies To

- All `src/app/partner/**`, `src/app/client/**`, `src/app/crew/**`, `src/app/track/**` pages and components
- Any dropdown, badge, tag, label, or tooltip that displays a status, stage, or type field from the database
- API responses that are directly rendered (no raw `snake_case` keys shown to users)
